Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.96,0:00:07.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With her death, Asseylum Vers Allusia, loyal\Ncountryman and beloved family member,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.21,0:00:12.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}has revealed the truth to us.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.39,0:00:18.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Through her pious act,\Nshe has opened our eyes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.93,0:00:23.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are meting out justice. The Earth\Nhas spat upon our good faith,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.53,0:00:27.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}heaped insult upon insult,\Nand now committed this atrocity!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.10,0:00:29.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is divine retribution\Nbrought down upon them!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.82,0:00:35.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today, the Vers Empire\Ndeclares war against Earth!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.00,0:00:42.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All clear in Block 63B.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.83,0:00:44.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All clear in Block 63C.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.04,0:00:46.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no sign that he has\Nescaped from the castle!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.84,0:00:48.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Track him down!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.25,0:00:49.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes, sir!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.59,0:00:53.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn that boy... How dare he use the\Naudience chamber without permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:00:56.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When he's found,\Nexecute him on the spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.64,0:00:59.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Abide a moment, Count Cruhteo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:00.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Saazbaum.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.68,0:01:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He is the son of Dr. Troyard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.06,0:01:08.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wish to question him regarding\Nhis father's Aldnoah research.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.86,0:01:11.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Might I trouble you\Nto take him alive?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.90,0:01:18.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right... Please tell me\Nwhat happened after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.70,0:01:22.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me about the orange Kataphrakt\Nthat Sir Vlad had been pursuing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.38,0:03:01.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Grandfather... Why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.35,0:03:05.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A formal declaration\Nof war, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.56,0:03:08.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just when we heard there was going\Nto be a cease-fire, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.44,0:03:11.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The war never stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.23,0:03:13.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Marito...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.69,0:03:16.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We all pretended not to\Nnotice, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.86,0:03:22.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the old fart said, that princess'\Ndeath opened our eyes to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.57,0:03:25.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:29.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum has\Nno desire for war!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.83,0:03:33.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She tried to act as a bridge of friendship\Nbetween Earth and Vers!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.21,0:03:38.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And she ended up being\Nthe spark that set it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.51,0:03:42.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is what they've\Nalways dreamed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.01,0:03:44.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Some righteous cause that would\Nlet them pull out all the stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.97,0:03:48.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that the Martians\Nsacrificed their own princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.81,0:03:50.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, your attention, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.27,0:03:52.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone assemble in\Nthe briefing room!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.52,0:03:54.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's up, Yuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.73,0:03:57.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please address me as\NWarrant Officer Kaizuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.57,0:04:00.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're now officially at war\Nwith them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.99,0:04:09.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As of right now, you are drafted\Ninto service as soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.95,0:04:12.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That means that you are to adhere\Nto military rules and regulations,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.33,0:04:15.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and are now obligated to carry out whatever\Nduties you are ordered to perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.04,0:04:18.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to seeing you\Nput all that you have learned to good use,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.42,0:04:20.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,go into battle\Nwith courage in your hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.80,0:04:25.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and come into your own as warriors who\Nsafeguard the peace and order of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.81,0:04:33.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This ship will now resupply and make\Nrepairs at Tanegashima Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.15,0:04:38.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, we will most likely\Nhead for United Earth HQ in Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:41.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, everyone, man your\Nstations immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.11,0:04:44.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is all. Dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.78,0:04:50.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Soma Yagarai, age 28. My specialties are\Nsurgery and psychosomatic medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:53.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever need counseling,\Nmy door is always open.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.50,0:04:58.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thank you for your help. We can\Nuse all the doctors we can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.25,0:04:58.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you see, my big sister Seylum has been too\Nsick to go to school for the longest time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.21,0:05:00.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If you'll excuse me, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.84,0:05:00.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.05,0:05:01.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Your Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.09,0:05:03.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.59,0:05:06.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is why Her Highness never\Nreceived any military training.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.80,0:05:09.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is far too frail\Nto be a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.14,0:05:11.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.52,0:05:14.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, on the other hand,\Ncan pilot a Kat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.31,0:05:18.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you're all grown up,\Nplease do, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.73,0:05:20.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will! 'Bye, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.65,0:05:24.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you call your sister\N"Your Highness"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.66,0:05:30.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,B-Because to me, Seylum\Nis my beloved princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.29,0:05:34.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please forgive my\Nfamiliar tone, Milady.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.79,0:05:37.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite all right, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.13,0:05:39.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.00,0:05:45.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How old are you? Everyone who had military\Ntraining in high school is being drafted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.18,0:05:49.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was kept out of school...\Nfor family reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.35,0:05:51.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Well, even if you're not\N fighting at the front,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.83,0:05:54.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there are plenty of things\Nyou can help with at the rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.77,0:05:59.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you like, you could even support\Neveryone as a volunteer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:04.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want to do your part to\Ndefend Earth from the Martians?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.49,0:06:15.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I a maintenance worker\Ninstead of a pilot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.62,0:06:18.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You did flunk piloting, Calm..
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.21,0:06:23.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mechanics are just as crucial to the war.\NWithout them, the Kats won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.96,0:06:27.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How am I supposed to waste those\Nguys if I'm stuck in the hangar?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.30,0:06:29.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't be so gung-ho.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.43,0:06:34.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These past 15 years, no one's\Nseen any real action.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.72,0:06:37.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those who did are all dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.31,0:06:38.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On the Martian side, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.02,0:06:43.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that friend and foe alike\Nare all virgins, same as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.32,0:06:45.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.40,0:06:49.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho, are you saying you-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:53.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You lived through it, Lt. Marito.\NIsn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.79,0:06:55.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:57.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The scorebook says otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.71,0:07:01.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Tanegashima Report\NI wrote got buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.42,0:07:04.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanegashima Report?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.38,0:07:08.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's where the fragments first fell\Nwhen the Moon was destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:10.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,during Heaven's Fall 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.97,0:07:15.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... But something came down there\Nbefore the Moon did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.31,0:07:19.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Martians.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:27.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We went up against those monster Martian\NKataphrakts in obsolete tanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.74,0:07:29.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We were wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.65,0:07:32.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right after that, the Hyper Gate\Nwent out of control on the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.66,0:07:35.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Heaven's Fall was set off\Nby the spacetime quake,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.16,0:07:37.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and those Martian bastards\Nwiped out the entire battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.37,0:07:41.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no physical evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:46.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My report was made out to be the ramblings\Nof a madman written in terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.34,0:07:48.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it was the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.55,0:07:52.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mars' Kataphrakts are way beyond what\NEarth's technology can produce.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, the end result\Nwill be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.43,0:07:59.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because Earth doesn't have\NAldnoah drives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.85,0:08:01.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Aldnoah drives...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.32,0:08:10.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fugitive located! He's in\Nthe Sky Carrier hangar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.36,0:08:12.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do not let him escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.96,0:08:25.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn him... How long is he going to\Ncontinue making me look the fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.05,0:08:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The basics are the same as the trainer...\NEven with the higher output,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.30,0:08:36.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if gravity and surface hardness\Nremain the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:40.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,its agility will only decrease to\Nthe extent that its weight increases.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.06,0:08:44.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just have to acclimate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.11,0:08:56.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this is where\Nyou were, Inaho.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.07,0:08:57.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.08,0:09:02.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It truly is lovely...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.16,0:09:05.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is a blue sky\Nthat unusual to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.79,0:09:09.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... Are you studying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.38,0:09:13.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm brushing up. I'm not sure\Nhow useful it will be, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.38,0:09:14.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.93,0:09:17.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because we don't\Nhave Aldnoah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.76,0:09:22.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this "Aldnoah" thing, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.27,0:09:31.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aldnoah is technology belonging to a supercivilization\Nthat was discovered in ancient ruins on Vers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.69,0:09:34.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the world your people call Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.64,0:09:39.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The first Terran to make\Ncontact and awaken it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.95,0:09:42.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,was Dr. Rayregalia Vers Rayvers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.95,0:09:47.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,my grandfather\Nand ruling emperor of Vers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:52.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aldnoah, activated after\Nso many eons,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.05,0:09:56.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,recognized Grandfather\Nas its rightful heir
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.26,0:10:01.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and burned the Aldnoah activation\Nfactor into his very genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.81,0:10:03.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.06,0:10:08.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The only ones with the innate ability\Nto activate Aldnoah are grandfather
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.98,0:10:11.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and his descendants.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.32,0:10:17.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange for the knights\Nswearing fealty to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.74,0:10:21.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he gave them Aldnoah\Nand its activation factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.66,0:10:24.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Using that power,\Nthe knights created
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.29,0:10:29.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,mighty castles and Kataphrakts\Nand ruled over the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.42,0:10:37.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now, those who settled the desolate\N lands of Mars have set their eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.13,0:10:40.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.88,0:10:44.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The cradle of all humanity, a land blessed\Nwith water and air in such abundance
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.60,0:10:49.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that they refract light to make\Nthe sea and sky appear blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:51.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.44,0:10:57.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The blue sky isn't caused by diffraction, but\Nthrough the effects of Rayleigh scattering.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:11:00.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Slaine said it was caused\Nby light diffraction...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.74,0:11:05.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The sky is blue from Rayleigh scattering,\Nclouds are white from Mie scattering.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.16,0:11:08.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your friend was mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.84,0:11:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.22,0:11:23.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be okay if I took over?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.72,0:11:25.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're a real go-getter, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.85,0:11:27.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to\Nget a feel for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.89,0:11:30.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you get in Docking?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:33.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, A-minus... sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.77,0:11:35.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we come into port,\Nstand next to me and watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:37.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, take your hands\Nout of your sleeves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.99,0:11:41.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir! Sorry, sir.\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.03,0:11:44.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't we going to get uniforms?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:49.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have enough. I'm hoping\Nwe can stock up at the next port.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.42,0:11:55.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't really feel right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.34,0:11:57.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why go to Tanegashima, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:12:00.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought this area\Nhad been sealed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.80,0:12:03.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With our intel on their\NLanding Castles so spotty now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.64,0:12:06.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we'd like to avoid any areas\Nthat are likely invasion targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.60,0:12:12.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanegashima is an area that was devastated so\Nbadly that the very landscape was altered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.69,0:12:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, there is no\Ncivilian population here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:17.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you think the Martians\Nthat came down in Tokyo
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.07,0:12:20.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,won't bother attacking\Nanything this far out?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.83,0:12:34.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought I'd come\Nback here like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:41.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a bit early for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.55,0:12:46.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't for me. It's for the ones\Nwho can't drink anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.10,0:12:51.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like John Humeray?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.27,0:12:59.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.74,0:13:02.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This one is for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.96,0:13:05.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jumping off the wagon.\NWant a belt, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.08,0:13:08.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.58,0:13:10.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mind if I join you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.45,0:13:13.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Capt. Magbaredge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:22.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Tanegashima Report. I've heard\Nrumors about it, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.38,0:13:27.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I never once believed\Nit was a fabrication.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.93,0:13:30.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's exactly why, Lt. Marito...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.35,0:13:33.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I have a particular\Ndislike for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.44,0:13:42.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That battle on Tanegashima...\NMy big brother fought in it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.11,0:13:49.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed in action.\NMurdered, rather. By you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.29,0:13:54.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Magbaredge is the name of\Nthe family that adopted me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.37,0:13:56.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My birth name was Humeray.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.29,0:14:01.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your best friend was my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.48,0:14:23.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy craft above Tanegashima!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.99,0:14:26.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anti-air combat! Take us out\Nto open water!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:27.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maximum combat speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.11,0:14:28.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,hard right rudder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.07,0:14:30.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me, ma'am?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.95,0:14:32.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damage report!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.08,0:14:35.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Missile impact, Block 18!\NNo detonation!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.75,0:14:38.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Appears to be a dud-\NNo, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.54,0:14:39.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.96,0:14:43.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's moving... It's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:52.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.31,0:14:53.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.61,0:15:02.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Helm not responding!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:03.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to collide!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.23,0:15:04.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All hands, brace for impact!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.93,0:15:37.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Entering my territory without\Nso much as a by your leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.93,0:15:40.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Such atrocious manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.40,0:15:45.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must rake you over the coals.\NRather hot ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.65,0:15:48.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it doing\Nthis far out?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.74,0:15:51.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This must be a different Martian\Nthan the one in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.66,0:15:53.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Order the shipboard Kats to launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.28,0:15:56.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Friesian Platoon, launch!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.33,0:15:58.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Raising elevator 1.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.21,0:16:02.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Calm!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.00,0:16:04.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This one isn't powering up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.17,0:16:06.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! We're running\Na systems check on that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.80,0:16:08.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give us a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.76,0:16:18.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's kinda cramped in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.68,0:16:20.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.81,0:16:25.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Force feedback\Nchecking program, start.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.65,0:16:28.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ejection seat functional.\NIFF confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.11,0:16:31.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tactical datalink, activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.57,0:16:33.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All systems green.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.04,0:16:41.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mustang Leader to Mustang 22.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.50,0:16:44.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nao, you're in a trainer,\Nso you be our marksman.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:46.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki? But your arm is still-
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.09,0:16:49.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If my newbie is fighting,\NI can't sit this out, can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.38,0:16:50.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Warrant Officer Kaizuka!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.84,0:16:52.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Yuki" is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.84,0:16:54.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Over and out!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.22,0:16:59.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.31,0:17:05.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mustang Leader, Warrant Officer\NYuki Kaizuka, now launching!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:09.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Raising elevator 2\Nand vehicle elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.65,0:17:13.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Friesian Platoon, deploy on the bow.\NMustang Platoon, you're on the stern.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.95,0:17:16.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All units, intercept airborne\Nflying weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.62,0:17:22.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I almost feel sorry for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.08,0:17:25.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you inferior race that does not\Npossess the Aldnoah drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.63,0:17:29.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cower before my power,\Nbow down before me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.80,0:17:31.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then despair and die!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.34,0:17:38.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fly, my messengers!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.15,0:17:54.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spread out! If you're clustered\Ntoo tight, you'll be sitting ducks!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.83,0:18:01.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, they're tough!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.83,0:18:06.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My fists are transformed into a single molecule.\NYour bullets are useless against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.17,0:18:09.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mustang Leader to all units! AP rounds\Nineffective against enemy's armor!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.96,0:18:12.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All units, switch over\Nto HE rounds and attack!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.59,0:18:13.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- R-Roger!\N- Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.47,0:18:15.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.30,0:18:18.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Marito!\NWhere are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.30,0:18:22.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm playing my home field again!\NI can take to the field, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:30.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or maybe this is\Nan away game...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.66,0:18:40.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inko, watch our back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.41,0:18:41.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.59,0:18:53.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On your feet!\NYou're a sitting duck there!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.17,0:18:57.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, ma'am!\NSorry, Inaho! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.88,0:18:59.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.72,0:19:00.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this one good to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.60,0:19:05.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Marito? No, that one's\Nstill being tuned!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.52,0:19:08.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it runs, right? I just\Nneed it to fire one shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.65,0:19:10.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Get a heavy barrel ready for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.11,0:19:14.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Damn... it....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.95,0:19:29.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on! What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.75,0:19:39.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Block 24 hit! Blocks 23, 24,\Nand 25 taking on water!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.68,0:19:41.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Evacuate the affected\Nblocks immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.22,0:19:44.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if we don't seal\Nthe bulkheads, we-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.39,0:19:45.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.97,0:19:48.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The ship is done for, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.35,0:19:51.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Abandon ship,\Nnoncombatants first!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.19,0:19:53.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Get the landing craft\Nprepped for launch ASAP!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.74,0:20:01.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:04.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.37,0:20:07.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please be careful, Milady!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.70,0:20:08.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.79,0:20:15.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy unit overhead\Nis in a nosedive!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.80,0:20:17.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Three others closing in\Nfrom our flanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.26,0:20:21.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They appear to be accelerating from\Na distance to build up speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.22,0:20:23.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's on a collision course\Nwith the bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.80,0:20:28.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have toyed with you for\Nlong enough. Now, die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:30.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.62,0:20:47.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.41,0:20:51.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Direct hit!\NNext, 3 mil right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.96,0:20:55.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not even HE rounds can destroy\Nthose things' armor plating.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.42,0:20:56.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.63,0:21:05.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...from this range, we can use the\Nblast pressure to throw it off course.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.64,0:21:07.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No sign of movement in\Nprimary enemy craft!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.31,0:21:09.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next! Left 7 mil!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.39,0:21:14.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Direct hit! Last!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.53,0:21:24.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We won't make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.04,0:21:31.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Out of ammo?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.20,0:21:32.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.75,0:21:35.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.46,0:21:42.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.14,0:21:47.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? We're alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.82,0:22:00.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
